# ChromaIntel Continuation Plan

This file is the autonomous backlog. Work top-down. Mark an item done only after code/docs/artifacts are updated, verification passes, and the milestone is committed.

## Current Baseline

- Repo is public at `https://github.com/namzhale/chromaintel`.
- Latest major implemented layer: SOTA-oriented CPU training and data extraction pipeline.
- Current verified tests: `32 passed` with project `.venv`.
- Current trained demo artifact exists at `data/processed/models/trained_forward_bundle.joblib`.
- Current processed model matrix is 15,052 rows and 3,945 compounds after RepoRT plus MCMRT expansion; quality target still provisional.

## Milestone A: Data Expansion And Canonical Ingestion

- [x] Add additional reviewed public RT sample imports beyond RepoRT dataset 0001.
- [x] Add a public-source manifest with source name, URL, license, expected fields, adapter status, and known missingness.
- [x] Extend local public import tests for CSV, TSV, JSON/JSONL, and XLSX where dependencies allow.
- [x] Add a canonical merge command that can combine multiple processed external samples with internal/mock data.
- [x] Preserve full provenance for every external row.

## Milestone B: Internal Lab Onboarding Maturity

- [x] Add `docs/internal_lab_onboarding.md` with realistic BE workflow instructions.
- [ ] Add template examples for accepted, failed, low intensity, poor resolution, and carryover cases.
- [x] Add validation for gradient consistency, ion mode vocabulary, matrix vocabulary, and required MS transition fields when ion mode is known.
- [x] Add an import preview report that summarizes missingness, invalid rows, and duplicate runs.

## Milestone C: Modeling And SOTA Path

- [x] Add grouped validation when enough rows exist; group by `inchikey`, `source_dataset`, and method family.
- [x] Add optional CatBoost/XGBoost support with graceful skip when packages are absent; LightGBM remains a future optional backend.
- [ ] Add Morgan fingerprint feature option in training CLI and compare with descriptor-only training. Feature option is implemented; full comparison run remains.
- [x] Add applicability-domain metadata to the persisted bundle and use it in `ForwardPredictor._out_of_domain`.
- [ ] Add conformal interval reporting by source/matrix/column family once calibration rows exist.
- [x] Add a research note for future GNN/Transformer transfer learning architecture and required data volume.

## Milestone D: Recommendation Engine Upgrade

- [x] Add score decomposition to recommendation outputs: RT fit, quality, runtime penalty, confidence, AD penalty.
- [ ] Make search-space bounds configurable from a checked-in YAML/JSON settings file.
- [ ] Add candidate constraints for available columns, solvent systems, pH range, flow range, temperature range, and max runtime.
- [x] Penalize out-of-domain candidates from trained bundle metadata.
- [x] Add tests for ranking stability and score decomposition.

## Milestone E: GUI/API Release Polish

- [ ] Add GUI import preview for literature-extracted and local-public processed CSVs.
- [ ] Add Model Evaluation page views for source metrics, feature significance, AD flags, and uncertainty interval.
- [ ] Add API tests for prediction, recommendation, and dataset browser endpoints.
- [ ] Smoke-test Streamlit and FastAPI locally.
- [ ] Add screenshots or placeholder screenshots only after GUI smoke passes.

## Milestone F: Release Discipline

- [ ] Run full verification in `.VERIFY`.
- [ ] Update README with any new commands.
- [ ] Regenerate reports intentionally.
- [ ] Commit the milestone.
- [ ] Push `main`.

## Next Recommended Slice

Next high-value slice:

1. Add checked-in search-space configuration for recommendation bounds.
2. Add method/column-family holdout metrics and wire them into the Russian PDF dashboard.
3. Add accepted/failed/low-intensity/poor-resolution/carryover rows to the internal lab template package.
4. Run core training plus optional Morgan comparison artifact if CPU time is acceptable.
5. Run full tests, training, commit, push.
